\begin_layout Problem
An advanced civilisation constructs two concentric massless shells around
 a neutron star of mass 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

.
 The inner shell has a circumference of 
\begin_inset Formula $6\pi GM$
\end_inset

 and the outer shell has a circumference of 
\begin_inset Formula $20\pi GM$
\end_inset

.
 What is the exact physical distance between the shells? 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We can get the radii of the two shells with 
\begin_inset Formula $C=2\pi r$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
6\pi GM & = & 2\pi r_{1}\implies r_{1}=3GM\\
20\pi GM & = & 2\pi r_{2}\implies r_{2}=10GM
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Now we use the metric to find the distance, noting that 
\begin_inset Formula $dt=d\theta=d\phi=0$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
ds^{2} & = & \frac{dr^{2}}{1-\frac{2GM}{r}}\\
ds & = & \frac{dr}{\sqrt{1-\frac{2GM}{r}}}
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the distance is given by
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\Delta s=\int ds=\int_{r_{1}}^{r_{2}}\frac{dr}{\sqrt{1-\frac{2GM}{r}}}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Using the change of coordinates 
\begin_inset Formula $u=\frac{2GM}{r}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $du=\frac{-2GM}{r^{2}}dr\,\implies dr=\frac{-r^{2}}{2GM}=\frac{-2GM}{u^{2}}du$
\end_inset

, and noting that 
\begin_inset Formula $u_{1}=\frac{2}{3}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $u_{2}=\frac{1}{5}$
\end_inset

, we get
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
\Delta s & = & \int_{r_{1}}^{r_{2}}\frac{dr}{\sqrt{1-\frac{2GM}{r}}}=\int_{u_{1}}^{u_{2}}\frac{-2GM}{u^{2}\sqrt{1-u}}du\\
 & = & -2GM\int_{u_{1}}^{u_{2}}\frac{1}{u^{2}\sqrt{1-u}}du=-2GM\Big(\frac{-\sqrt{1-u}}{u}-\tanh^{-1}(\sqrt{1-u})\Big)\Bigg|_{u_{1}}^{u_{2}}\\
 & = & -2GM\Big(\frac{-\sqrt{4/5}}{1/5}-\tanh^{-1}(\sqrt{4/5})+\frac{\sqrt{1/3}}{2/3}+\tanh^{-1}(\sqrt{1/3})\Big)\\
 & = & -2GM\Big(-4.47-1.44+0.87+0.66)\\
\Delta s & = & 8.76GM
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If the space were flat, this distance would be 
\begin_inset Formula $7GM$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

